Observational Study of Historical Behavior of Interest and Inflation Rates in Brazil and USA

Introduction:

  • We gather inflation and interest rates between the USA and Brazil to find a relationship between their distributions. We will compare each country’s descriptive statistics to come to a conclusion.
  • If their distributions are similar we gain no new information and therefore there is no relationship between the two countries. Otherwise, we say that there is a relationship between them.
  • We also want to investigate whether the inflation and interest rates are dependent (positively associated) so that we can understand if a change in interest rate drive a change in inflation rate.

With the recent increase in inflation rates around the world.

CPI: The Consumer Price Index is a measure of inflation and the buying habits of urban consumers. - It includes prices for food, clothing, shelter, transportation, services, and sales taxes. - The index is calculated by averaging price changes with weights representing their importance in consumer spending.

  • The CPI is an index, to compute the annualized inflation rate, we need to compute (cpi_t12/cpi_0), since we have monthly data.
  • The interest rate is already annnualized
